A vintage 1950s-style illustration depicting a chaotic office scene where multiple workers sit around a large circular table, each person facing outward with their backs to the center, arms crossed in frustration. Papers and folders float suspended in mid-air between them, never quite reaching anyone. The color palette features muted mustard yellows, burnt oranges, and olive greens typical of mid-century design. Each worker is dressed in period-appropriate attire, their expressions showing visible exasperation and disconnect. In the center of the table sits an elaborate but completely tangled web of colored strings connecting nobody to anything useful. The composition emphasizes isolation despite physical proximity, with subtle visual barriers like potted plants and filing cabinets creating invisible walls between the figures. The overall mood captures the absurdity of coordination without actual coordination, everyone busy yet nothing productive happening.
